"'''Passages'''" is a short story written by [[Charlene Newcomb]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 7|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 7]] by [[West End Games]] in August 1995.

==Plot summary==
[[Tere Metallo]], [[Captain/Legends|captain]] of the [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] ''[[Star Quest]]'', takes on a down-on-his-luck [[Technician|mechanic]], [[Matt Turhaya]], as part of her crew. During an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] crackdown on [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] activity on [[Kabaira]], an [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial officer]] identifies Matt as a [[Desertion/Legends|deserter]] and [[Prison/Legends|arrests]] him. Tere frees Matt, as well as several other [[Prisoner/Legends|captive]] [[Rebel trooper/Legends|Rebels]], with the help of the local underground.

After Matt loses to Tere in a [[Sabacc/Legends|sabacc]] game in [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], he becomes the co-[[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] of the ''Star Quest''.

==Continuity==
[[Charlene Newcomb|Charlene Newcomb's]] story connected to her larger [[Alexandra Winger|Alex Winger]] series, though this tale was set many [[Standard year/Legends|years]] before it. [[Matt Turhaya|Matt]] mourned the [[Death/Legends|loss]] of [[Anii Degarienne|his wife]] and young daughter, the [[Gender/Legends|girl]] who would grow up to be Alex Winger after being adopted into a [[Tork Winger|prominent family]] on [[Garos IV]].<ref name="TERC" />

The placement of this tale was left ambiguous on Charlene Newcomb's original timeline; however, Alex Winger's age at the time of her adoption<ref name="Mission to Zila">{{JournalCite|3|Mission to Zila}}</ref><ref name="Rendezvous with Destiny">{{JournalCite|6|Rendezvous with Destiny}}</ref> suggests that this tale takes place in [[3 BBY/Legends|3]] or [[2 BBY/Legends|2 BBY]]. Though existence of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] may seem to indicate 2 BBY, ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' places it in 3 BBY.

